{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Ping @mrdoob. Any news on this?\nAFAIK the exporter handles the face materials correctly. It is just ignored in the loader.\n\nI have a modified ObjectLoader somewhere that solved the issue for me if that would be of any use. \n","created_at":"2015-12-30T16:23:43.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480#issuecomment-168027895","id":168027895,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2ODAyNzg5NQ==","updated_at":"2015-12-30T16:23:43.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/168027895","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3514740?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hekto","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MTQ3NDA=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hekto","type":"User","id":3514740,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hekto\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Yes, that's a known issue. Haven't been able to tackle it yet...\n","created_at":"2015-12-30T20:39:46.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480#issuecomment-168070115","id":168070115,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2ODA3MDExNQ==","updated_at":"2015-12-30T20:39:46.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/168070115","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I ran into this problem yesterday and spent half the night with my debugger figuring out exactly why MultiMaterials are not created by ObjectLoader although the information is present in the exported geometries. After I had a solution hacked together I found this, and I would love to discuss it.\n\nFrom a quick experiment it looks like this could be fixed with just a few tweaks here and there. I have to admit that I don't know very much about how the JSON-Format is being used and developed except for my few use-cases in exporting from blender to three.js. \n\nI would propose adding a property `materials` (as alternative to `material`) to the `object` JSON-structure for objects where the geometries use face-materials. \n\nThis would look something like this and would likely be backward-compatible:\n\n``` javascript\n      {\n        \"name\": \"singleMaterial\",\n        \/* ... *\/\n        \"material\": \"A8094C11-04FC-3C4E-98FF-7CEB861372DA\",\n        \"geometry\": \"C2B97B3F-B625-304C-935C-8209B4B0A178\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"multiMaterial\",\n        \/* ... *\/\n        \"geometry\": \"0A4F7562-D188-3F99-B596-5908E44CB0BD\",\n        \"materials\": [\n          \"CFD25A0F-52CC-3690-9E40-7535F3B67FE6\",\n          \"88D87DF2-EF89-34A8-802B-55EAC788EDEF\"\n        ]\n      }\n```\n\nHandling these would only require a small change in the `getMaterial()`-function within `ObjectLoader.parseObject()`:\n\n``` javascript\n\/\/ ObjectLoader.js, line 463:\nfunction getMaterial( name ) {\n\n  if ( Array.isArray( name ) ) {\n\n    return new THREE.MultiMaterial( name.map( getMaterial ) );\n\n  }\n\n  \/\/ ... handle the regular case as before (i.e. return material from `materials`-map)\n\n}\n```\n\nAnd everywhere where it is called:\n\n``` javascript\n\/\/ ObjectLoader.js, line 517 (in case 'Mesh':)\nobject = new THREE.Mesh( getGeometry( data.geometry ),  getMaterial( data.material || data.materials ) );\n```\n\nWhat do you think? Is this something I could propose a PR for?\nI am currently looking into what would need to be changed in the blender-exporter to have it properly export that materials-array, but that is probably something I could just as well solve by preprocessing the JSON-structure before parsing.\n","created_at":"2016-02-14T15:45:06.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480#issuecomment-183906983","id":183906983,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE4MzkwNjk4Mw==","updated_at":"2016-02-14T15:45:06.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/183906983","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/158792?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/usefulthink","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1ODc5Mg==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"usefulthink","type":"User","id":158792,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/usefulthink\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"As for the blender-exporter, I think it should be possible to store the UUID generated for the material somewhere in the blender material-properties so it can be looked up when preparing the meshes for export. The material-information per geometry would then need to propagate to where the object-declarations are assembled.\n","created_at":"2016-02-14T16:56:04.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480#issuecomment-183923715","id":183923715,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6480","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE4MzkyMzcxNQ==","updated_at":"2016-02-14T16:56:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.